      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. Increased border security is essential to protect national sovereignty and ensure that only those who meet our legal standards can enter the country.\n2. Stricter immigration enforcement helps maintain public safety by preventing illegal activities, such as human trafficking and drug smuggling, that often accompany undocumented immigration.\n3. A robust immigration system ensures that resources are allocated fairly and that citizens have access to jobs, healthcare, and education without being overwhelmed by an influx of new arrivals.\n4. Stronger border security and immigration enforcement can help deter potential migrants from attempting dangerous and illegal routes, thus reducing the risk of loss of life and human suffering.\n5. By enforcing immigration laws, we uphold the rule of law and demonstrate that everyone, regardless of their status, is subject to the same legal standards and consequences.",
